      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 87: A high-priority background push with no `pt` is treated as a call push and triggers a full reconnect plus the longer call grace window. The comment on isDhtProxyCallWakeup says FCM priority must not be used as a fallback because regular DHT values default to high priority, so this branch reintroduces exactly that misclassification. This can wake the daemon unnecessarily for message/sync pushes and undermine the battery-saving goal. Remove the priority-only fallback or restrict it to a protocol-guaranteed call signal. Suggested change: `val isCallPush \u003d isCallNotification || isDhtProxyCallWakeup(remoteMessage)`.",
      "revId": "bdc3c413803208b0cc50093e0125d7a03a243a8c",
