      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done in PS23 via the explicit-disable marker (your second alternative). The executor-ordering variant was rejected on purpose: it restores the PS18 race in the opposite direction (queued restore undoing the explicit deactivation), and even ordered correctly it cannot close the stale-isActive window since volatile details update asynchronously. The marker is authoritative regardless of queue order: checked before deactivate-and-record, re-checked in the restore loop, cleared on explicit reactivation and removeAccount().",
