      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 47: Disabling push restores accounts and then immediately calls setProxyEnabled(false). If restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() reactivates the recorded proxy accounts, setProxyEnabled(false) can leave those accounts active with proxy disabled, changing the previous contract where proxy-enabled accounts were the only ones forced active. This can keep background connections alive even after the user disables push. Restore should be followed by applying the intended account active policy for non-proxy accounts, or setProxyEnabled(false) should explicitly preserve/restore the user\u0027s desired active state. Suggested fix: after disabling the proxy, explicitly deactivate only accounts that were active solely because of proxy/push, or move this state transition into AccountService so restore and proxy-disable are atomic and respect user intent.",
      "revId": "bdc3c413803208b0cc50093e0125d7a03a243a8c",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
